    <h1>SleepTone - Support</h1>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>How do I play sounds in the background?</h3>
    <p>Tap any sound to start playing it. You can then lock your screen or switch to another app — SleepTone will continue playing. You can control playback from the lock screen or notification center without reopening the app.</p>

    <h3>How do I mix multiple sounds?</h3>
    <p>Tap the "+" button to add sounds to your mix. Free users can mix up to 2 sounds simultaneously. Premium users can mix up to 5 sounds. Adjust each sound's volume independently using the sliders.</p>

    <h3>How does the sleep timer work?</h3>
    <p>Tap the timer icon to set a sleep timer. Choose from 15, 30, 60, or 90 minutes (Premium users can set any duration from 1 to 480 minutes). When the timer expires, SleepTone gradually fades out over 30 seconds so you won't be woken by a sudden stop.</p>

    <h3>Do I need an internet connection?</h3>
    <p>No. All 42 sounds are bundled with the app and work completely offline. No streaming, no buffering, no Wi-Fi required.</p>

    <h3>How do I restore my Premium subscription?</h3>
    <p>Open SleepTone, go to the Premium screen, and tap "Restore Purchases". Your subscription will be restored automatically if you have an active subscription linked to your Apple ID or Google account.</p>

    <h3>How do I cancel my subscription?</h3>
    <p>Subscriptions are managed through your Apple ID or Google Play account, not through SleepTone directly.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>iOS:</strong> Go to Settings > [Your Name] > Subscriptions > SleepTone > Cancel Subscription</li>
        <li><strong>Android:</strong> Go to Google Play Store > Menu > Subscriptions > SleepTone > Cancel</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Are there intrusive ads?</h3>
    <p>No. SleepTone shows only a small banner ad for the first 5 minutes of playback, then it disappears automatically. There are no pop-ups, video ads, or interstitial ads. Premium removes all ads entirely.</p>

